# Crono backend — layer boundaries

API base: `/api/v1` · Stack: TypeScript, Express 5, Prisma, BullMQ, Zod.

## Layers

| Layer | May | Must NOT |
|-------|-----|----------|
| **routes** | mount path, middleware | DB queries, business rules |
| **controllers** | read req, call service, set status | prisma calls, bcrypt, Stripe |
| **services** | rules, orchestration, `ApiError` | `req`/`res`, DB access |
| **repositories** | Prisma queries via `@crono/db` client | auth decisions, HTTP |

## Packages (infra only)

- `@crono/db` — Prisma client, schema, migrations, types. No feature queries.
- `@crono/queue` — Redis + BullMQ queue export.
- `@crono/shared` — pure helpers (`generateApiKey`, `isValidCron`, constants).

## When user asks to "add a feature"

List files per layer first. User implements bottom-up: repository → service → validation → controller → route.

## Mentor mode still applies

Unless user says **fix it**, do not paste full implementations — describe what each file should do and how to test.
